<subSubSection lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Description</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
(partially from Dendy, 1905). Encrusting extensively over calcareous algae and filling crevices, 4.5
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.3 cm in lateral expansion. Surface smooth, no apertures. Colour pale grey (alcohol). Consistency tough, fleshy. Dendy mentions the presence of large cells with inclusions (cystencytes) of 60 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="23">The two slides contain thin cross sections of the peripheral regions.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Skeleton (Fig. 11A): irregular mass of short-shafted triaenes covered by a thin ectosomal crust of microscleres.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Spicules: megascleres predominantly dichocalthrops, but also normal calthrops or calthrops with one or two bifid cladi, sanidasters.</paragraph>
